  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "We automatically collected relevant data by extracting from the code submissions at the three key milestones in the project timeline.",
    "Listing 1: An example illustrating how comments are used to annotate AI-generated code.1 #pragma once 2 #include <utility> 3 #include <vector> 4 #include <string> 5 // ai-gen start (gpt3, 0) 6 struct vectorHash { 7 std::size_t operator () (const std::vector<std::string> vect) const { 8 std::size_t seed = 0; 9 for (const std::string& str: vect) { 10 seed ^= std::hash<std::string>{}(str)+0x9e3779b9 + (seed << 6) + (seed >> 2); 11 } 12 return seed; 13 } 14 }; 15 // ai-gen end User StudyWe conducted an online survey using the Unified Theory of Acceptance and Use of Technology (UTAUT) model by Venkatesh et al. [19].",
    "The study aims to capture the interaction between behavioral intention and the usage behavior of AI code generation, incorporating key constructs such as Performance Expectancy (PE), Effort Expectancy (EE), Social Influence (SI), and Facilitating Conditions (FC).",
    "The model is further enriched by incorporating moderating factors called personal influence factors.",
    "Namely past internship experience, student workload, and coding ability."
  ],
